sud///////////////////////////////////////////////////////
///   How to Get iSight Cameras Working on Ubuntu   ///
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////

1. Install the `isight-firmware-tools` package:
o
	$ sudo apt-get install isight-firmware-tools

   At the prompt, "Extract firmware from Apple driver?", choose <No>.

2. Copy the AppleUSBVideoSupport file into /lib/firmware (this file
   is located in the same directory as this README).

3. Run the following command:

	$ sudo ift-extract -a /lib/firmware/AppleUSBVideoSupport

You should be good to go.  :)
